<dl class="document-metadata dl-invert row">
	
	    <dt class="col-md-3 blacklight-readonly_title_tesim">Title:</dt>
		<dd class="col-md-9 blacklight-readonly_title_tesim">
		    Letter from the Public Library of Science [to signers of the PLoS open letter]
		</dd>
		
	
	    <dt class="col-md-3 blacklight-readonly_creator_tesim">Creator:</dt>
		<dd class="col-md-9 blacklight-readonly_creator_tesim">
		    <a href="/web/20231030052829/https://profiles.nlm.nih.gov/spotlight/mv/catalog?f%5Breadonly_creator_ssim%5D%5B%5D=Public+Library+of+Science">Public Library of Science</a>
		</dd>
		
	
	    <dt class="col-md-3 blacklight-readonly_date_tesim">Date:</dt>
		<dd class="col-md-9 blacklight-readonly_date_tesim">
		    31 August 2001
		</dd>
		
	
	    <dt class="col-md-3 blacklight-readonly_description_tesim">Description:</dt>
		<dd class="col-md-9 blacklight-readonly_description_tesim">
		    This letter, reproduced on the PLOS web site, was sent to all the signers of the original open letter, letting them know that while over 26,000 scientists had pledged to stop dealing with non-open-access publishers, there were still lots of publishers that hadn&#39;t met the conditions of the open letter. PLOS urged support for those that did, and noted that it planned to start publishing.
		</dd>
		
	
	    <dt class="col-md-3 blacklight-readonly_location_tesim">Location:</dt>
		<dd class="col-md-9 blacklight-readonly_location_tesim">
		    Box: 15. Folder: 18
		</dd>
		
	
	    <dt class="col-md-3 blacklight-readonly_rights_tesim">Rights:</dt>
